SIMPLE: unconformability
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unconformability
<hw>Un`con*form`a*bil"i*ty</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
quality or state of being unconformable; unconformableness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Lack of parallelism between one
series of strata and another, especially when due to a disturbance of
the position of the earlier strata before the latter were
deposited.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unconformable</ent>⟦br⟧
